    </div>
    <div aria-hidden="true" style="position:absolute;left:-1rem;top:0.5rem;z-index:1;font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(10rem,20vw,16rem);font-weight:700;line-height:1;color:transparent;-webkit-text-stroke:1px rgba(196,162,78,0.18);pointer-events:none;user-select:none;">L</div>
    <div aria-hidden="true" style="position:absolute;right:-0.5rem;bottom:-1.5rem;z-index:1;font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(12rem,24vw,20rem);font-weight:700;line-height:1;color:transparent;-webkit-text-stroke:1px rgba(124,92,191,0.15);pointer-events:none;user-select:none;">P</div>
    <div style="position:relative;z-index:2;max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;width:100%;">
      <p class="p-label" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;color:var(--color-soft-gold);opacity:0.9;">Complete Guide</p>
      <div class="p-divider" style="margin-bottom:1.75rem;"></div>
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(2.6rem,6.5vw,4.75rem);font-weight:700;line-height:1.08;color:#f5f0e8;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin:0 0 1.5rem;text-shadow:0 2px 20px rgba(14,10,26,0.6);">
        Life Path Number in<br><em style="color:#c8a8f0;font-style:italic;">Numerology</em>
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.8;color:rgba(240,234,255,0.82);max-width:560px;margin:0 auto 2.5rem;text-shadow:0 1px 8px rgba(14,10,26,0.5);">
        Your life path number is the single most important number in your numerology chart. It reveals your core purpose, natural strengths, recurring challenges, and the overall direction your life is meant to take.
      </p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.875rem;justify-content:center;">
        <a href="https://8904b5z1168aar3k8annz7y61n.hop.clickbank.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:var(--color-violet);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;transition:background 0.2s,transform 0.15s;box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(124,92,191,0.45);" onmouseover="this.style.background='#6a4eab';this.style.transform='translateY(-1px)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--color-violet)';this.style.transform='none'">Get My Free Reading →</a>
        <a href="#calculator" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);backdrop-filter:blur(6px);color:#f5f0e8;font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;padding:0.875rem 1.75rem;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;border:1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);transition:border-color 0.2s,background 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.15)';this.style.borderColor='rgba(255,255,255,0.4)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='rgba(255,255,255,0.08)';this.style.borderColor='rgba(255,255,255,0.2)'">Calculate My Number ↓</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Author byline -->
  <div style="background:var(--color-light-bg);padding:1.5rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
      <img src="/images/author-maddi-green.webp" alt="Maddie Greene" style="width:3rem;height:3rem;border-radius:50%;object-fit:cover;flex-shrink:0;border:2px solid rgba(124,92,191,0.2);box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(26,21,40,0.08);" />
      <div>
        <p style="color:var(--color-body-text);font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 0.15rem;">Written by <strong>Maddie Greene</strong></p>
        <p style="color:var(--color-muted-text);font-size:0.8rem;margin:0;">Numerology writer &amp; researcher</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content + Sticky sidebar wrapper -->
  <div class="xl:flex xl:gap-6 xl:max-w-[1200px] xl:mx-auto xl:px-4">
    <!-- Main content column -->
    <div class="xl:flex-1 xl:min-w-0">

  <!-- What is a Life Path Number -->
  <section style="padding:3.5rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;background:var(--color-card-bg);">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto xl:mx-0 xl:max-w-none">
      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.5rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
        What Is a Life Path Number?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Your life path number is a single digit, or one of the master numbers 11, 22, or 33, calculated from your full date of birth. It's the one number in your chart that never changes. You could change your name, move countries, completely reinvent yourself, and your life path number stays the same. That's part of why practitioners treat it as the starting point for any reading.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Each number in numerology carries a distinct energy. Your life path number is the energy you were born into. If you're familiar with astrology, think of it like a sun sign - except it's based entirely on your birth date rather than the position of a celestial body. People who share a life path number tend to have recognisable similarities in how they approach the world, what drives them, and what trips them up. It's not destiny, exactly. More like a recurring theme.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The reason practitioners focus on this number first is that it colours everything else. Your career choices, the way you handle conflict, the kinds of people you keep ending up around - a lot of that connects back to the energy of your life path number. Understanding it doesn't hand you a roadmap. But it does tell you something true about the terrain you're working with.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Unlike the name-based numbers in your numerology chart (expression number, soul urge number, personality number), the life path number can't be changed by any decision you make. It came with you. That fixed quality is either reassuring or unsettling depending on your relationship with self-knowledge.
      </p>

      <!-- Callout box -->
      <div style="background:var(--color-light-bg);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-left:4px solid var(--color-soft-gold);border-radius:8px;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);line-height:1.8;margin:0;">
          <strong style="color:var(--color-body-text);">Worth knowing:</strong> Your life path number describes your natural energy and recurring themes. It's not a ceiling. Plenty of people live out the shadow side of their number for years before the penny drops and they start working with it instead of against it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Calculate -->
  <section id="calculator" style="padding:4rem 1.5rem;background:var(--color-light-bg);border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto xl:mx-0 xl:max-w-none">
      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.5rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 1rem;">
        How to Calculate Your Life Path Number
      </h2>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;line-height:1.8;color:var(--color-muted-text);margin:0 0 2.5rem;">
        Calculating your life path number uses a straightforward method: reduce your full date of birth to a single digit (or master number) by adding each component separately. Here's the method numerologists use.
      </p>

      <!-- Calculator -->
      <div class="card-light p-6 md:p-8 mb-10">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
            <div>
              <label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-body-text mb-2" for="lp-calc-month">Month</label>
              <select id="lp-calc-month" class="w-full p-3 text-base text-body-text bg-white border-2 border-border rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:border-violet transition-colors">
                <option value="">Month</option>
                <option value="1">January</option>
                <option value="2">February</option>
                <option value="3">March</option>
                <option value="4">April</option>
                <option value="5">May</option>
                <option value="6">June</option>
                <option value="7">July</option>
                <option value="8">August</option>
                <option value="9">September</option>
                <option value="10">October</option>
                <option value="11">November</option>
                <option value="12">December</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div>
              <label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-body-text mb-2" for="lp-calc-day">Day</label>
              <input type="number" id="lp-calc-day" min="1" max="31" placeholder="e.g. 15"
                class="w-full p-3 text-base text-body-text bg-white border-2 border-border rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:border-violet transition-colors" />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-body-text mb-2" for="lp-calc-year">Year</label>
              <input type="number" id="lp-calc-year" min="1900" max="2025" placeholder="e.g. 1990"
                class="w-full p-3 text-base text-body-text bg-white border-2 border-border rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:border-violet transition-colors" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <button id="lp-calc-btn" style="width:100%;background:var(--color-violet);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border:none;border-radius:6px;cursor:pointer;margin-bottom:0.5rem;transition:background 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#6a4eab'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--color-violet)'">Calculate My Life Path Number</button>
          <div id="lp-calc-error" class="hidden text-center text-sm text-red-500 mt-3 mb-2"></div>

          <div id="lp-calc-result" class="hidden mt-6">
            <div style="background:var(--color-light-bg);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:8px;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
              <p style="font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-soft-gold);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.18em;margin:0 0 1rem;">How your number was calculated</p>
              <div class="space-y-3 font-mono text-sm" id="lp-working-steps"></div>
            </div>
            <div style="text-align:center;padding:1.5rem 0;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);margin:0 0 0.5rem;">Your Life Path Number is</p>
              <div id="lp-result-number" style="font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--color-violet);line-height:1;margin-bottom:0.5rem;"></div>
              <div id="lp-result-label" style="display:inline-block;background:rgba(196,162,78,0.1);color:var(--color-gold);font-weight:600;padding:0.25rem 0.875rem;border:1px solid rgba(196,162,78,0.35);border-radius:20px;font-size:0.75rem;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:1.25rem;"></div>
              <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);line-height:1.7;margin:0 auto 1.5rem;max-width:28rem;" id="lp-result-blurb"></p>
              <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:center;">
                <a id="lp-result-guide-link" href="#" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:var(--color-violet);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:0.95rem;padding:0.875rem 1.75rem;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;">Read Your Life Path Guide →</a>
                <a href="https://8904b5z1168aar3k8annz7y61n.hop.clickbank.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:transparent;color:var(--color-body-text);font-weight:600;font-size:0.9rem;padding:0.875rem 1.75rem;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;border:1.5px solid var(--color-border);">
                  Get a Free Full Reading
                </a>
              </div>
              <p style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);margin-top:0.75rem;">Free reading via Numerologist.com, no payment required</p>
            </div>
          </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Steps -->
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 0.4rem;font-size:0.95rem;">Separate your birth date into DD / MM / YYYY</h3>
            <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);line-height:1.7;margin:0;">Write out your full date of birth as three separate components: the day, the month, and the year. For example: born 15 March 1990 = Day: 15 | Month: 03 | Year: 1990.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 0.4rem;font-size:0.95rem;">Reduce each component to a single digit</h3>
            <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 0.5rem;">Add the digits of each component until you reach a single digit <em>or</em> a master number (11 or 22).</p>
            <div class="step-code">
              Day: 15 → 1+5 = <strong>6</strong><br />
              Month: 03 → <strong>3</strong><br />
              Year: 1990 → 1+9+9+0 = 19 → 1+9 = <strong>10</strong> → 1+0 = <strong>1</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 0.4rem;font-size:0.95rem;">Add the three results together, then reduce again</h3>
            <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 0.5rem;">Add your three reduced numbers. If the result is two digits and isn't a master number, reduce again to a single digit.</p>
            <div class="step-code">
              6 + 3 + 1 = <strong>10</strong> → 1+0 = <strong>Life Path 1</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-num alert">!</div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 0.4rem;font-size:0.95rem;">Stop at 11, 22, or 33, these are master numbers</h3>
            <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--color-muted-text);line-height:1.7;margin:0;">Master numbers 11, 22, and 33 are never reduced further. If your total reaches one of these at any stage, keep it. These carry amplified energy and responsibility in numerology.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <a href="/learn/how-to-calculate-life-path-number/" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--color-violet);text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">
          See full guide with worked examples →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Life Path Numbers Grid -->
  <section id="meanings" style="padding:5rem 1.5rem;background:white;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
    <div style="max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <p class="p-label" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">All 9 Numbers</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 0.75rem;">
          Life Path Numbers 1–9: Meanings &amp; Traits
        </h2>
        <div class="p-divider" style="margin:0 auto 1.25rem;"></div>
        <p style="color:var(--color-muted-text);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;">
          Each number carries a distinct vibration, set of strengths, and life challenges. Find yours below.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1.5rem;">
        {lpNumbers.map(lp => (
          <a href={lp.href} class="feat-card" style="text-decoration:none;">
            <div class="feat-img-wrap">
